# Edit BBEdit keybinding/keyboard shortcuts
Preferences>Menus & Shortcuts
# May be custom edited shortcuts
^L  = Open Language Menu # for syntax highlighting
^O  = Open Text Options
Find Windows:
^⇧N    = Case Sensitive
^⇧E    = Entire Word
^⇧G    = Use Grep
^⇧M    = Show Matches
^⇧S    = Selection Only
^⇧W    = Wrap Around
^⇧H    = Open Search History Menu
^⇧P    = Open Saved Patterns Menu
^⇧C    = Open Pattern Cheat Sheet
^⇧down = Swap Search & Replace Fields

# useful options to enable
Preferences>Editing>Allow pinch-to-zoom to change magnification
Preferences>Editing>Display instance of selected text>underline
                    # better for dark mode/low contrast highlight
Preferences>Editing>Allow single-click line selection
# 
Preferences>Editor Defaults>Spaces per tab: 4
# 
Preferences>Completion>Include system text replacements in completion list
                       # requires paid licence to Pro?
# 
Preferences>Keyboard>Use Tab key to navigate Placeholders
Preferences>Keyboard>"Home" and "End" key behavior:
                      - Scroll to beginning and end of document
Preferences>Keyboard>Allow Tab key to indent text blocks
Preferences>Keyboard>Enable Shift-Delete for forward delete
Preferences>Keyboard>eferences>Keyboard>Enable macOS "Help" key
Preferences>Keyboard>When auto-indenting, remove leading white space from indented line
Preferences>Keyboard>Allow Page Up and Page Down keys to move the insertion point
Preferences>Keyboard>Option-up and option-down move by paragraphs
# 
Preferences>Sidebar>Add documents to sidebar in alphabetical order
                    # disable to add new/opened docs to end of list
# 
Preferences>Text Colors
            # modify syntax highlighting colors per color scheme & language
            # alternately you can switch color theme from here (vs in Appearance)

# Keyboard navigation
in addition to standard Mac option/command navigation shortcuts
    option-right/left  = move cursor by "word"
    command-right/left = jump to beginning/end of line
BBEdit supports standard readline keybindings:
    control-A = jump to beginning of line
    control-E = jump to end of line

    
